                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">
                           <locus from="3r" to="62v">3r-62v</locus>: by lesser trained hand. <locus from="63r" to="109r">63r-109r</locus>: mediocre but careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        <date>Second half of the 19th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; the incipits of subsections of the
                           text; a few words like färiha (fol. 9r), yǝśmǝrǝwwo (fol. 11r), ba-fǝrhat
                           (14r), ʾǝndalä (16r) and qalǝnnät (fol. 20r); elements of the punctuation
                           signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.
 On the incipit page of Text I
                           (fol. 3r), few lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand a: fols
